           contain  the  system-wide  and terminal dependent LITES2 initialisation
           files.

           On later systems, LSL$LITES2CMD  is  a  search  list,  running  through
           LSL$SITE_ROOT:[LITES2.CMD],  then through all [.CMD] directories on the
           public tree.

        o  LSL$LITES2JNL points to a directory into which LITES2 writes a  journal
           file  of  commands  given during a session (extension .LJN).  This will
